metadata.name: Playground II #113
metadata.description:
"Playground II" is a Free abstract generative animated artwork. 
A giveaway/gift for the new year 2024!

Happy new year to all !!

CONTROLS
KEYS:

- 1-2: Set resolution from 1x to 2x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save current screen in a 3x Resolution PNG
- A: Toggle Slideshow Mode (changes every 10 secs)
- Spacebar: Toggle Animation
- H: Toggle a Help Screen
- R: Reset - reload

MOUSE:

- Click: Generate new graphics

----
Made with p5js and custom shaders

metadata.name: Polyptych #54
metadata.description:
Polyptych is a 3D interactive installation inspired by generative plotter designs. It is also meant to be displayed as multiple prints taken from different angles, be it a diptych, triptych, tetraptych, or more.

For an example see: https://bgo.la/polyptych.png

Instructions:

- use the mouse to navigate around the piece (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'space' to pause the animation
- press 'p' to take a screenshot in a custom resolution (always 1:1 ratio) of the current view. Note that taking a screenshot will only work when seeing the piece live (click 'Open live' on fxhash), not on the mint page because of the sandboxed iframe.

Berlin, December 2021
@bgola

metadata.name: Balanced #245
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: Life has no scores #195
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop ‚ÄúNothing comes from nothing‚Äù. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press ‚Äò2‚Äô to save png.

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Drei #68
metadata.description:
For Lia Drei (https://www.archivioguerrieridrei.com/biografia-1?lang=en)

This morning I thought about all the work I did with triangles... the idea came to me that the right triangle is the symbol of creation...(‚Ä¶)
The hypotenuse is the love that unites and gives life. The tip of the triangle is the uterus which makes the space grow.
-- LIA DREI (Diaries, 2004)

My paintings have no past, they are empty of meaning in the present, but await the discussions of the future, as remotely as possible.
And this is why they don't have their feet firmly planted in the ground, although there are invisible roots that take life from the earth, like so many blades of grass.
While I work I look for the truth in what I do. The time is not yesterday because it would be false, it is not today because the emotion takes my breath away and I die every moment and am reborn after every new brushstroke.
Soon after, time becomes old, useless, meaningless. I never know what will come out with the next brushstroke or spatula stroke.
My thoughts go at supersonic speed and only stop to choose another color. The one just painted is never the right one. So I live the life of the new painting with the sense of mystery that the moonless night has. (‚Ä¶)
-- LIA DREI (Notes, 1962)

----

I never talk about myself.

I'm not creative.
I blatantly steal other people's art.
I'm a bad coder, I copy, paste, mix ideas.
I often ruin it, degrade it.
But I always make it mine what I like.

I absorb.

-- ALESSANDRO FIORE (fxhash, 2024)


‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

The work is created responsive by default and it will adapt to the browser window. It will change (even consistently in some cases) based on the screen aspect ratio.

Key commands:

1 = Square 2000x2000
2 = Square 4000x4000
3 = Square 6000x6000 (Dependent on your browser limitations, tested on Safari (Mac))
p = Portrait 1500x2115
l = Landscape 2115x1500
e = Responsive/Default
f = Fullscreen
s = Save as image


See LICENSE.txt in live view for licensing details.

metadata.name: Hexagones - Art for Bots #48
metadata.description:
Not for Humans.

Sometimes after rapid drops, bots are set up to watch for blockchain contracts and activity, often getting in on the action before people with wallets and using UI front-ends can. Price your drop too low, and the bots will scoop everything up before anyone has seen anything.

Sometimes we make art for the bots. They wait, watch, and buy and flip before moving on, indifferent to what they see and do. These (coincidentally Twitter icon orientated) hexagons will make the bots hearts go [beep] [boop], before becoming hexagones.

Instructions ::

h - toggle high-res
s - download and save image

metadata.name: All√©gories bool√©ennes #448
metadata.description:
"All√©gories bool√©ennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ "a": Play the animation
‚Ä¢ "s": Export the image (default 2160‚Ää√ó‚Ää3840px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480‚Ää√ó11520px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320‚Ää√ó‚Ää7680px PNG)
‚Ä¢ "n": Back to 2160‚Ää√ó‚Ää3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Broken Symmetries #1/3 #34
metadata.description:
"It was the best of times, it was the worst of times, it was the age of wisdom, it was the age of foolishness, it was the epoch of belief, it was the epoch of incredulity, it was the season of Light, it was the season of Darkness, it was the spring of hope, it was the winter of despair, we had everything before us, we had nothing before us..."
                                      Charles Dickens

This piece is the first in a planed series of three intended as studies on composition.

It is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- 1 : render @ original resolution
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
- s : download canvas as SVG @ current resolution; This can be used with a plotter.

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #147
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect ‚Äúfx(haish) - the Generator‚Äù
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your ‚Äúfx(haish) - The AI City‚Äù based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.

metadata.name: Fictional Cityscapes #100
metadata.description:
Some of the most stunning, and beloved, images are large cities, viewed from afar at the right angle, and preferably with some water in front. 

This project comes from my experiments with line art, and is slightly inspired by Hevey's amazing Dencity drop, which is on a different level to most generative art. 

The cities here are based on some fictional tower architecture and some unusual skies.
